{"bookId": "69048808ef55966cf1d71f1d", "moduleId": "6909cd14d60676ac599cb644", "subjectId": "69075cb049e6141a77a59709", "chapterId": "69075cb149e6141a77a59717", "subject": "IOQM", "chapter": "Matrices", "count": 1, "questions": [{"id": 306348, "subject": "IOQM", "chapter": "Matrices", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "Olympiad workbook", "q": "Let $\\mathrm{P}_0=(3,1)$ and define $\\mathrm{P}_{\\mathrm{n}+1}=\\left(\\mathrm{x}_{\\mathrm{n}}, \\mathrm{y}_{\\mathrm{n}}\\right)$ for $\\mathrm{n} \\geq 0$ by\n$x_{n+1}=-\\frac{3 x_n-y_n}{2}, y_{n+1}=-\\frac{x_n+y_n}{2}$\n\nFind the area of the quadrilateral formed by the points $\\mathrm{P}_{96}, \\mathrm{P}_{97}, \\mathrm{P}_{98}, \\mathrm{P}_{99}$.", "options": ["A", "B", "C", "D"], "answer": 0, "solution": "$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\mathrm{P} \\equiv(3,1) \\\\\n& \\mathrm{P}_1 \\equiv(-4,-2) \\\\\n& \\mathrm{P}_2 \\equiv(5,3) \\\\\n& \\mathrm{P}_3 \\equiv(-6,-4)\n\\end{aligned}$\nfrom shifting\n$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text { area } & =\\frac{1}{2}\\left|\\begin{array}{llll}\n3 & 5 & -4 & -63 \\\\\n1 & 3 & -2 & -41\n\\end{array}\\right| \\\\\n& \\frac{1}{2}(9-5-10+12+16-12-6+12) \\\\\n& =8 \\text { Ans. }\n\\end{aligned}$", "difficulty": "Hard", "source": "Olympiad workbook", "_book": "69048808ef55966cf1d71f1d", "_chapterKey": "69048808ef55966cf1d71f1d__6909cd14d60676ac599cb644__69075cb049e6141a77a59709__69075cb149e6141a77a59717"}]}